Privacy Policy
Caffly AI

Last updated: June 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how Caffly AI ("the App," "we," "us," or "our") handles information when you use our iOS application. By using the App, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use the App.

1. Overview
Caffly AI is a caffeine tracking and sleep insights application. We are designed to keep your personal data on your device and in your private iCloud account wherever possible. We do not sell your personal information.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 Information you provide
Profile and onboarding information, such as your name, goals, caffeine sensitivity, body weight, bedtime preferences, and related settings you enter during setup or in the App.

Caffeine logs, including drink type, caffeine amount, timestamps, notes, and optional photos you attach to entries.

Sign in with Apple information, if you choose to sign in. Apple may provide a stable user identifier and, on first sign-in only, your name and email address (including Apple's private relay email if you use Hide My Email).

2.2 Information from your device and permissions
Apple Health (HealthKit) data, if you grant permission. We read sleep-related data to show how caffeine may relate to your sleep. We do not write data to HealthKit.

Camera and photo library, if you grant permission, to capture or select images of drinks for logging and analysis.

Notifications, if you grant permission, to deliver local reminders such as caffeine cutoff alerts.

2.3 Subscription and purchase information
Subscription status and related purchase metadata are processed through Apple In-App Purchase and RevenueCat, our subscription management provider. We receive information needed to confirm whether you have an active subscription. We do not receive or store your full payment card details.

2.4 AI-assisted features
If you use camera scanning or similar AI features, images or text you submit may be sent to Google Firebase / Gemini for processing to identify drink details and caffeine estimates. Do not submit images or content you are not comfortable sharing for this purpose.

2.5 Automatically collected information
The App may store technical and usage-related data locally on your device (for example, app preferences and sync state). We do not operate third-party advertising analytics in the App at this time.

3. How We Use Information
We use the information described above to:

Provide caffeine tracking, metabolic estimates, sleep-related insights, and personalized features

Sync your drink logs across your devices through your private iCloud account

Authenticate your identity when you use Sign in with Apple

Manage subscriptions and restore purchases

Send local notifications you enable

Process images and text through AI services when you use those features

Improve reliability, security, and support for the App

4. How We Store and Sync Data
On your device: Profile settings, preferences, and app state are stored locally.

iCloud (CloudKit): Drink logs and related Core Data records may sync through your private iCloud container associated with your Apple ID. This data is encrypted in transit and protected by Apple's iCloud security. We do not operate our own servers for this synced content and cannot access your private iCloud database.

On your device only: Some settings (such as metabolic tuning stored outside Core Data) may remain on the device and are not synced via iCloud unless otherwise stated in the App.

